snippet.textDisplay: Beautiful song and composition. Bonobibi is also worshipped by both Hindu and Muslim people of Sunderbans in Bengal before they go out in the jungle to do something. Bonobibi is the protector of forest and the people who live in the forest. The poor fishermen and honey collecter often fall prey to the tigers and crocodiles while they go out to make a living, that's why they pray to Bonobibi, the goddess/protector of the forest and it's believed that she has saved many people from tigers and crocodiles. And this beautiful presentation truly potrays the beauty of forest and the people who live in the heart of the forest. Onek bhalobasa coke studio bangla ke❤️
